WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:02.537
<i>Kenny: This year, my family's
learning to be supportive</i>

00:02.538 --> 00:03.667
<i>of each other's changes,</i>

00:03.668 --> 00:06.195
<i>even if that change is
upsetting, confusing,</i>

00:06.196 --> 00:08.154
<i>or really hard to see.</i>

00:08.156 --> 00:10.055
What do you think?

00:10.056 --> 00:11.881
About?

00:11.882 --> 00:13.065
My mustache.

00:13.066 --> 00:14.851
Here. You can see it
better in this angle.

00:15.002 --> 00:16.075
You see it?

00:16.076 --> 00:19.125
I want to be there for
you, but I don't see it.

00:19.126 --> 00:20.145
[Muffled] It's r... it's right...

00:20.146 --> 00:22.175
Oh, wh... wait. There it is.

00:22.176 --> 00:25.065
You look like the old lady who
sells shaved ice in the park.

00:25.066 --> 00:26.105
Yes.

00:26.106 --> 00:28.065
Kenny, what's this about play auditions?

00:28.066 --> 00:30.175
What? Did you go through my backpack?

00:30.176 --> 00:31.975
Well, why didn't you tell me

00:31.976 --> 00:33.085
you're auditioning for the school play?

00:33.086 --> 00:35.025
You know the theater's our thing.

00:35.026 --> 00:38.065
<i>For years, Mom and I have been
the Doris Day and Rock Hudson</i>

00:38.066 --> 00:39.205
<i>of our church's
theater productions.</i>

00:39.206 --> 00:43.155
Oh, Balthazar, I'm so glad
you didn't forget the myrrh.

00:43.156 --> 00:46.075
And the frankincense was so reasonable!

00:46.076 --> 00:49.085
Pat, did you know Kenny was
auditioning for the school play?

00:49.086 --> 00:50.240
Oh, yeah. It's all anybody's talking

00:50.265 --> 00:51.145
about down in the basement.

00:51.146 --> 00:53.085
Kenny, why would you keep it a secret?

00:53.086 --> 00:55.005
You used to tell me everything.

00:55.006 --> 00:56.055
If I didn't feel so comfortable

00:56.056 --> 00:57.125
rifling through your
personal belongings,

00:57.126 --> 00:58.195
I wouldn't know anything about you.

00:58.196 --> 01:01.085
Kenny: Look, I didn't
tell anybody about this.

01:01.086 --> 01:03.095
You know, I've wanted
to do it for a long time,

01:03.096 --> 01:05.055
but I was afraid of
being outed at school.

01:05.056 --> 01:07.165
So, you know, now that everyone knows,

01:07.166 --> 01:09.065
there's nothing stopping me.

01:09.066 --> 01:10.175
You can do a bunch of stuff now.

01:10.176 --> 01:13.035
You can be a male cheerleader
or a male ballerina,

01:13.036 --> 01:15.095
or you can be one of those
shirtless guys at Abercrombie.

01:15.096 --> 01:17.175
Well, I'm working on the play
and currently heterosexual.

01:17.176 --> 01:19.035
Currently?

01:19.036 --> 01:20.185
We'll see what happens in college.

01:20.186 --> 01:22.185
Anyhoo, I'm in charge
of the special effects.

01:22.186 --> 01:24.135
It's gonna be super gory.

01:24.136 --> 01:26.045
Gory? I thought you were
doing "Romeo and Juliet"?

01:26.046 --> 01:27.175
"Zombie Romeo and Juliet."

01:27.176 --> 01:29.125
It's our drama teacher's re-imagining

01:29.126 --> 01:31.035
of the classic play.

01:31.036 --> 01:33.065
Ms. Hanson felt like
Shakespeare phoned it in.

01:33.066 --> 01:34.075
Dad, could you get me

01:34.076 --> 01:36.035
some crime-scene photos for reference?

01:36.036 --> 01:37.975
Oh, I-I-I-I don't
know about that, honey.

01:37.976 --> 01:39.616
I think they might be
a little unsettling.

01:41.116 --> 01:44.065
Holy [Bleep].

01:44.066 --> 01:47.045
I made it in shop class.

01:47.046 --> 01:48.065
I'm gonna throw up.

01:48.066 --> 01:50.995
If you promise never, ever to do that

01:50.996 --> 01:53.985
never, ever again, I
will get you some photos.

01:53.986 --> 01:55.065
Excellent. Got to go.

01:55.066 --> 01:56.195
No, no, young lady.

01:56.196 --> 01:58.205
Not until you've cleaned the
blood off the breakfast table.

01:58.206 --> 02:00.995
[Sighs] Wait, Kenny.

02:00.996 --> 02:02.205
It says here Ms. Hanson's looking for

02:02.206 --> 02:04.155
some parent volunteers.

02:04.156 --> 02:06.035
It sounds like she could use some help.

02:06.036 --> 02:07.294
[Chuckles] I could do that.

02:07.436 --> 02:09.175
<i>I do want to make her happy,</i>

02:09.175 --> 02:13.105
<i>but making her happy will
probably make me sad.</i>

02:13.106 --> 02:15.075
Um... Y-yeah.

02:15.076 --> 02:16.145
Okay.

02:16.146 --> 02:18.095
Yay! Theater buddies.

02:18.096 --> 02:20.135
- Yay.
- I promise, you won't regret it.

02:20.136 --> 02:22.035
Oh.

02:22.036 --> 02:24.975
There's no hugging me
at school, though, okay?

02:24.976 --> 02:26.480
You can let go any time. [Chuckles]

02:26.597 --> 02:30.014
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
- www.Addic7ed.com -

02:30.196 --> 02:33.005
I'm so excited.

02:33.006 --> 02:35.085
Treading the boards together again.

02:35.086 --> 02:37.135
[Inhales deeply] Oh,
the smell of the theater.

02:37.136 --> 02:40.125
I was talking to Ms. Hanson.
She seems a little overwhelmed.

02:40.126 --> 02:41.195
I am very overwhelmed.

02:41.196 --> 02:42.195
To be honest, I thought this would be

02:42.196 --> 02:43.490
a little more like "Glee."

02:43.618 --> 02:45.075
That was my main
preparation for this job,

02:45.076 --> 02:46.075
watching "Glee."

02:46.076 --> 02:47.105
Thank god you're here.

02:47.106 --> 02:48.195
I thought there'd be way more gay kids.

02:48.196 --> 02:52.095
That one really threw me.

02:52.096 --> 02:56.995
Girl, I have to say, your
eyebrows are on fleek.

02:56.996 --> 02:59.045
Stuart, stop it. You go over there.

02:59.046 --> 03:01.115
Okay, I need everyone to focus.

03:01.116 --> 03:03.115
Focus up, okay?

03:03.116 --> 03:06.065
All right. Kenny, do you know Mimi?

03:06.066 --> 03:08.145
Oh, we know each other.
He was my boyfriend.

03:08.146 --> 03:10.055
Then he came out as gay.

03:10.056 --> 03:12.095
So I know him, yeah.

03:12.096 --> 03:13.985
Drama.

03:13.986 --> 03:16.075
It's all happening.

03:16.076 --> 03:20.005
Mimi, we're both
auditioning for the play.

03:20.006 --> 03:22.005
- It's so fun.
- Super fun.

03:22.006 --> 03:23.155
Yeah, you've come to the one place

03:23.156 --> 03:25.125
where I didn't have to be
reminded of your deception.

03:25.126 --> 03:27.076
Awesome.

03:29.036 --> 03:31.016
[Fingers snap]

03:32.186 --> 03:36.125
[Sighs] Both my special gals are here.

03:36.126 --> 03:38.185
Yay.

03:38.186 --> 03:40.185
So, Pat, what kind of crime-scene photos

03:40.186 --> 03:41.519
are you looking for, exactly?

03:41.548 --> 03:43.115
Oh, you know, anything gory, really.

03:43.116 --> 03:45.105
Uh, any missing limbs.

03:45.106 --> 03:47.175
Uh, any bludgeonings
you have would be great.

03:47.176 --> 03:50.185
Um, just nothing too hard-core,
because it is for my daughter.

03:50.186 --> 03:52.185
- That's so sweet.
- Ah.

03:52.186 --> 03:54.185
- What is Shannon now, 14?
- Yeah.

03:54.186 --> 03:57.095
That's when I started looking
at crime-scene photos, too.

03:57.096 --> 04:00.095
Look at me now, working in
the crime-scene photo department.

04:00.096 --> 04:02.085
Dreams, huh?

04:02.086 --> 04:04.025
I'm gonna send you some
of my personal favorites.

04:04.026 --> 04:05.065
Great. Thank you.

04:05.066 --> 04:06.145
- Hey.
- Hmm?

04:06.146 --> 04:09.105
