04:33.996 --> 04:36.085
"O, that I were a glove upon that hand

04:36.086 --> 04:38.185
that I might touch that rotting cheek."

04:38.186 --> 04:41.095
Oh, that was not good.

04:41.096 --> 04:43.045
How's the scene going?

04:43.046 --> 04:45.175
Well, I don't seem to
be able to express emotion

04:45.176 --> 04:47.115
like a person, or even a zombie.

04:47.116 --> 04:50.025
I mean, Siri read it
with more emotion than I did.

04:50.026 --> 04:51.105
This play is a travesty.

04:51.106 --> 04:54.055
But if you want Romeo,
you can make it happen.

04:54.056 --> 04:55.075
Could you help me?

04:55.076 --> 04:57.065
I mean, you obviously have the range.

04:57.066 --> 04:59.195
You have played everything
from Jezebel to the Holy Mother.

04:59.196 --> 05:03.105
That was quite an Easter.

05:03.106 --> 05:06.005
<i>Announcer: And with one
minute left to go in the game... </i>

05:06.006 --> 05:08.005
- Hey.
- Dad, I know you've been wondering

05:08.006 --> 05:09.986
why I grew this mustache.

05:11.086 --> 05:15.155
Um... Well, I just figured you
wanted to look like Tom Selleck.

05:15.156 --> 05:16.155
[Laughs]

05:16.156 --> 05:18.015
The grandpa on "Blue Bloods"?

05:18.016 --> 05:20.205
[Sighs]

05:20.206 --> 05:22.125
What do you need, son?

05:22.126 --> 05:24.995
There's a girl at
school that I really like.

05:24.996 --> 05:26.985
- Mm-hmm.
- Her name is Lacey...

05:26.986 --> 05:29.005
Uh, which I assume is
short for Laceandra.

05:29.006 --> 05:31.045
Probably not, but continue.

05:31.046 --> 05:32.055
Well, you know I've always been

05:32.056 --> 05:34.115
kind of known for my verbal skills.

05:34.116 --> 05:36.205
Again, continue.

05:36.206 --> 05:38.085
But there's [Sighs]

05:38.086 --> 05:39.145
There's something wrong with me.

05:39.146 --> 05:41.195
I-I've been kind of off my game lately.

05:41.196 --> 05:44.065
