05:47.016 --> 05:48.986
What? Hey, Lacey. What's up?

05:50.006 --> 05:51.095
Books, huh?

05:51.096 --> 05:54.055
Uh... Yeah.

05:54.056 --> 05:55.075
Books.

05:55.076 --> 05:56.075
Books.

05:56.076 --> 05:59.046
Booksssssss.

06:01.116 --> 06:03.025
'Cause you, uh...

06:03.026 --> 06:05.975
Ca... you like cat... Cats.

06:05.976 --> 06:07.055
Y-you're probably good with women.

06:07.056 --> 06:08.085
Well, sure.

06:08.086 --> 06:09.195
I mean, I don't like to brag,

06:09.196 --> 06:13.125
but I have used words to
talk to women before.

06:13.126 --> 06:16.025
Sounds like your first line was fine.

06:16.026 --> 06:18.975
I think that... that we... you...

06:18.976 --> 06:23.185
one would need to just
kind of follow that up.

06:23.186 --> 06:25.175
You know?

06:25.176 --> 06:27.095
- Huh.
- Hmm.

06:27.096 --> 06:29.005
Interesting.

06:29.006 --> 06:30.055
Yeah, that's right.

06:30.056 --> 06:33.115
Just don't worry about what to say.

06:33.116 --> 06:36.995
Just keep talking, and the
rest will happen on its own.

06:36.996 --> 06:39.015
- Just keep talking.
- Yeah.

06:39.016 --> 06:40.145
- That's solid.
- Right?

06:40.146 --> 06:42.155
You know, like...
like we're talking right now.

06:42.156 --> 06:44.185
You know, no big deal.

06:44.186 --> 06:47.035
I mean, a girl's just a dad in a skirt.

06:47.036 --> 06:49.016
Right?

06:51.126 --> 06:53.975
Emotional scenes can be tough.

06:53.976 --> 06:55.045
But there are tricks.

06:55.046 --> 06:58.075
For example, if you want to act sad,

06:58.076 --> 07:00.095
look down at a spot on the floor.

07:00.096 --> 07:01.995
Mm-hmm.

07:01.996 --> 07:03.195
If you need to be thoughtful,

07:03.196 --> 07:08.055
pretend you're watching a
bird flying slowly across the sky.

07:08.056 --> 07:09.095
- Mm?
- Okay.

07:09.096 --> 07:11.145
Um, what about here, when I say,

07:11.146 --> 07:16.135
"It is my undead lady, O, it
is my decomposing love."?

07:16.136 --> 07:20.145
Clench your butt real
tight and think about pancakes.

07:20.146 --> 07:22.720
That doesn't really sound...

07:22.721 --> 07:24.135
Who got five out of five rosaries

07:24.136 --> 07:27.975
in the church bulletin for
her portrayal of Bathsheba?

07:27.976 --> 07:30.035
Okay.

07:30.036 --> 07:32.016
[Clears throat]

07:36.116 --> 07:42.025
It is my undead lady, O,
it is my decomposing love.

07:42.026 --> 07:46.155
See how she leans her
cheek upon her cold, dead hand.

07:46.156 --> 07:49.095
O, that I were a glove upon that hand

07:49.096 --> 07:54.055
that I might touch that rotting cheek.

07:54.056 --> 07:55.115
End scene.

07:55.116 --> 07:58.165
I knew I'd find my gay!

07:58.166 --> 08:03.095
I think we can all agree that
we have found our zombie Romeo.

08:03.096 --> 08:05.165
And, Stuart,
congratulations, you are his understudy.

08:05.166 --> 08:07.045
Outrageous!

08:07.046 --> 08:09.286
I'm being discriminated
against because I'm heterosexual.

08:10.976 --> 08:13.185
[Door opens, closes]

08:13.186 --> 08:15.115
That was amazing.

08:15.116 --> 08:18.145
I can't believe that
pancake butt-clench thing worked.

08:18.146 --> 08:20.155
It was purely theoretical until now.

08:20.156 --> 08:22.205
I couldn't have done this without you.

08:22.206 --> 08:24.985
I'm... I'm really glad you're here.

08:24.986 --> 08:27.015
Oh! So am I.

08:27.016 --> 08:29.025
