"Pooped"? Oh...

12:16.749 --> 12:18.838
Oh, we can't seat Cousin
Ronnie next to his sister.

12:18.839 --> 12:20.818
They haven't spoken since
the family reunion.

12:20.819 --> 12:21.868
Oh, man. That got ugly.

12:21.869 --> 12:23.758
I've never seen
anyone throw potato salad

12:23.759 --> 12:24.908
with so much precision.

12:24.909 --> 12:26.858
Well, it wasn't a great time
to find out you were adopted.

12:26.859 --> 12:27.819
[Gasps]

12:28.769 --> 12:29.948
Oh, Romeo!

12:29.949 --> 12:32.938
Oh, look how handsome on his big night!

12:32.939 --> 12:35.778
Uh, well, it... it fits.

12:35.779 --> 12:37.838
I'm still not sure it's
better than my regular costume.

12:37.839 --> 12:39.768
Oh, yes. Ms. Hanson and I agreed.

12:39.769 --> 12:40.858
This is what
Shakespeare would've wanted.

12:40.859 --> 12:42.908
Yeah, but it's gonna
get blood all over it.

12:42.909 --> 12:46.728
No, I swapped out Shannon's blood
cannon for a rice cannon.

12:46.729 --> 12:47.938
That doesn't make any sense.

12:47.939 --> 12:49.908
Yeah, she's not happy about it, either.

12:49.909 --> 12:52.768
Okay. Ha ha!

12:52.769 --> 12:54.848
I found the good camera.
It is out of film, though,

12:54.849 --> 12:55.788
so we're gonna have
to stop by the fotomat

12:55.789 --> 12:56.808
on the way to the school.

12:56.809 --> 12:58.808
Pat, I told you about this two days ago.

12:58.809 --> 12:59.908
- Oh, I forgot the flash cubes.
- [Sighs]

12:59.909 --> 13:01.738
Wait, what is going on?

13:01.739 --> 13:03.928
Why is Dad taking photos
with the old-timey camera?

13:03.929 --> 13:05.788
And is that a seating chart?

13:05.789 --> 13:07.878
No, it's not a seating chart.

13:07.879 --> 13:10.858
It's just a chart telling
us where everyone's gonna sit.

13:10.859 --> 13:11.908
The reception's open seating.

13:11.909 --> 13:13.928
- The reception?
- Uh, the cast party.

13:13.929 --> 13:15.798
In Europe, it's called a reception.

13:15.799 --> 13:17.918
They also call
bathrooms toilets. [Laughs]

13:17.919 --> 13:19.808
It's gonna be fabulous.

13:19.809 --> 13:21.908
What... why are you acting
like this is a real wedding?

13:21.909 --> 13:23.379
Don't be ridiculous.

13:23.380 --> 13:24.788
I don't think this is a real wedding.

13:24.789 --> 13:25.788
Wedding cake's here.

13:25.789 --> 13:26.908
[Sighs]

13:26.909 --> 13:29.838
Guy said it serves 100.

13:29.839 --> 13:31.958
- Thanks.
- [Smacks lips]

13:31.959 --> 13:33.918
[Clears throat]

13:33.919 --> 13:34.938
I see what you're doing.

13:34.939 --> 13:36.320
You're using the play

13:36.321 --> 13:37.898
to get me and Mimi back together again.

13:37.899 --> 13:39.788
I-I promise you,

13:39.789 --> 13:41.878
I am not trying to get you
and Mimi back together.

13:41.879 --> 13:44.748
She is the last girl on
earth I would want you to marry.

13:44.749 --> 13:45.958
- She's terrible.
- You're lying.

13:45.959 --> 13:48.818
I am not lying. I just...

13:48.819 --> 13:49.818
You just what?

13:49.819 --> 13:51.838
I just...

13:51.839 --> 13:53.768
This is the only chance I'm gonna have

13:53.769 --> 13:55.919
to see you marry a woman.

13:57.909 --> 13:59.818
Wait. That's what this is about?

13:59.819 --> 14:01.888
Yes. And I don't see
what the big deal is.

14:01.889 --> 14:02.938
[Sighs]

14:02.939 --> 14:05.868
Is it too much to ask to
have some pictures of you

14:05.869 --> 14:07.778
with a girl in a white dress?

14:07.779 --> 14:09.808
And some nice cake afterwards

14:09.809 --> 14:12.758
while a string
quartet plays Josh Groban?

14:12.759 --> 14:13.938
Oh, my god.

14:13.939 --> 14:16.778
I've been making mom porn!

14:16.779 --> 14:19.778
Where are you going? The
play's in 40 minutes!

14:19.779 --> 14:22.728
I don't care. I'm done with the play.

14:22.729 --> 14:23.788
You can go have your
precious hetero wedding

14:23.789 --> 14:24.928
with someone else.

14:24.929 --> 14:26.809
[Door slams]

14:31.176 --> 14:34.055
How'd you know where to find me?

14:34.056 --> 14:35.975
Come on. You've been running
away to the garage

14:35.976 --> 14:38.005
since you were 4 years old.

14:38.006 --> 14:41.125
Remember, you got so upset
Martha Stewart went to jail?

14:41.126 --> 14:43.045
They were making an example of her.

14:43.046 --> 14:44.512
[Laughs]

14:45.452 --> 14:47.125
Well, look, buddy, [Clears throat]

14:47.126 --> 14:49.115
you don't have to go through
with this if you don't want to.

14:49.116 --> 14:50.115
Okay?

14:50.116 --> 14:53.975
But, uh, your mom feels a little bad,

14:53.976 --> 14:55.165
and she's pretty upset.

14:55.166 --> 14:56.206
So am I.

14:58.046 --> 15:00.005
You know, I was just
starting to feel like,

15:00.006 --> 15:01.975
you know, maybe we
were getting close again.

15:01.976 --> 15:03.125
And then...

15:03.126 --> 15:04.175
I don't know.

15:04.176 --> 15:06.085
She's never going to
accept that I'm gay.

15:06.086 --> 15:08.975
No, I think she is. I think she is.

15:08.976 --> 15:11.205
I think this whole bizarre wedding
play is proof of that.

15:11.206 --> 15:13.055
Please, tell me how.

15:13.056 --> 15:15.025
Well, not too long ago,

15:15.026 --> 15:17.005
she was trying to turn
you straight, okay?

15:17.006 --> 15:18.155
And now I think that
she's really accepted

15:18.156 --> 15:21.125
the fact that you're
never gonna marry a woman.

15:21.126 --> 15:24.015
And for her, that is progress.

15:24.016 --> 15:28.015
It's incredibly
slow, very weird progress,

15:28.016 --> 15:29.165
but it's progress nonetheless.

15:29.166 --> 15:31.145
And that's pretty huge for her.

15:31.146 --> 15:34.006
Stop making me feel
like she has feelings.

15:36.086 --> 15:41.185
Well... Just remember that, uh,

15:41.186 --> 15:43.065
you've had 16 years

15:43.066 --> 15:45.145
to get used to the fact
that you're gay, okay?

15:45.146 --> 15:47.116
We've only had six weeks.

15:54.006 --> 15:57.025
So, the whole Martha
Stewart thing, and still no idea?

15:57.026 --> 15:59.015
Really?

15:59.016 --> 16:02.145
I'll admit, not my
finest detective work.

16:02.146 --> 16:04.723
♪ ♪

16:07.146 --> 16:09.176
[Grunting]

16:10.156 --> 16:11.195
My Romeo!

16:11.196 --> 16:12.206
Oh!

16:17.076 --> 16:20.185
Juliet, thy father canst
ne'er stop us now.

16:20.186 --> 16:22.065
Wilt thou be my wife?

16:22.066 --> 16:23.155
Yes!

16:23.156 --> 16:26.055
I finally understand why
people go to the theater.

16:26.056 --> 16:28.185
My bounty is as boundless as the sea.

16:28.186 --> 16:31.035
You're just in time to
see our son's ex-girlfriend

16:31.036 --> 16:33.075
marry an effeminate zombie.

16:33.076 --> 16:35.105
Oh, all right.

16:35.106 --> 16:39.155
["Pachelbel's Canon" plays]

16:39.156 --> 16:43.035
Romeo, ghostly death canst part us.

16:43.036 --> 16:47.096
I shall hunt for brains
with thou tilst the end of time.

16:49.076 --> 16:51.025
- I object to this wedding!
- [Music stops]

16:51.026 --> 16:52.145
[Audience murmurs]

16:52.146 --> 16:54.165
That zombie is a liar!

16:54.166 --> 16:56.115
I am your Romeo!

16:56.116 --> 16:58.976
Bitch, you have got to be kidding me.

17:02.976 --> 17:05.984
He came back.

17:05.986 --> 17:07.065
- Oh, my god.
- Oh, no.

17:07.066 --> 17:08.974
The audience is gonna
be totally confused.

17:08.976 --> 17:10.115
I know. It's just like "Glee."

17:10.116 --> 17:12.165
[Music resumes]

17:12.165 --> 17:16.175
I, Romeo, take you, Juliet,

17:16.175 --> 17:22.115
to have and to eat brains
with all the days of my life,

17:22.116 --> 17:24.165
which, barring any
unforeseen blunt trauma to the head,

17:24.165 --> 17:26.035
should be forever.

17:26.036 --> 17:29.045
I now bind thee as man and wife.

17:29.046 --> 17:30.185
You may kiss your undead bride.

17:30.186 --> 17:32.125
<i>Here it goes.</i>

17:32.126 --> 17:34.165
<i>If it helps my mom take
a tiny step forward,</i>

17:34.166 --> 17:36.604
<i>then the show must go on.</i>

17:37.146 --> 17:39.135
[All gasp]

17:39.136 --> 17:40.205
Sorry, Mom.

17:40.206 --> 17:43.025
But that was so much cooler than rice.

17:43.026 --> 17:45.175
Man: Geez. I've never seen that before.

17:45.176 --> 17:46.975
It's a bloodbath!

17:46.976 --> 17:47.995
- Ms. Hanson: Just like "Glee"!
- Yeah!

17:47.996 --> 17:49.055
[Cheers and applause]

17:49.056 --> 17:51.045
Can someone explain this to me?

17:51.046 --> 17:57.015
♪ Everybody's on the same page ♪

17:57.016 --> 18:00.065
♪ No new chapters ♪

18:00.066 --> 18:03.155
I'm sorry things didn't
work out with Lacey, buddy.

18:03.156 --> 18:05.036
No.

18:06.026 --> 18:08.155
I did not grow this
mustache for nothing.

18:08.156 --> 18:11.045
Honestly, I still don't see
it. Wait, I wasn't finished.

18:11.046 --> 18:12.085
Oh, boy.

18:12.086 --> 18:14.075
Laceandra. Hi. Hey.

18:14.076 --> 18:15.155
H... uh, hey. Listen.

18:15.156 --> 18:17.115
I am not good at this.

18:17.116 --> 18:19.195
But I want you to know th...

18:19.196 --> 18:21.095
uh, there was this one
time in the cafeteria,

18:21.096 --> 18:23.065
we were both eating lucky charms,

18:23.066 --> 18:26.112
and we noticed that we both like
to pick out the blue moons.

18:26.240 --> 18:28.985
Anyway, uh...

18:28.986 --> 18:31.985
I felt like we
really had a moment there.

18:31.986 --> 18:36.125
Or... or ma-maybe that
was just all in my head.

18:36.126 --> 18:38.005
It... yeah, it was probably all... yeah.

18:38.006 --> 18:39.115
I'm gonna... this
was... sorry. I'm sorry.

18:39.116 --> 18:41.985
No, no, no, no. It
wasn't just in your head.

18:41.986 --> 18:43.135
Blue moons are for freaks.

18:43.136 --> 18:44.205
[Chuckles]

18:44.206 --> 18:46.025
Whew!

18:46.026 --> 18:47.115
Right. Yeah.

18:47.116 --> 18:48.175
So, how'd you know my full name?

18:48.176 --> 18:50.185
What else could it be?

18:50.186 --> 18:52.045
- Oh, my god. Yeah.
- Right?

18:52.046 --> 18:54.195
♪ I don't care what they think ♪

18:54.196 --> 18:59.035
♪ No, I'm not listening ♪

18:59.036 --> 19:01.085
Honey, I'm sorry I tried to force you

19:01.086 --> 19:03.185
to live out my dream of
seeing you marry a girl.

19:03.186 --> 19:06.175
Oh, please. That old cliché again?

19:06.176 --> 19:08.085
I really did start out

19:08.086 --> 19:10.105
just wanting to spend
more time together,

19:10.106 --> 19:13.185
but things just... Got away from me.

19:13.186 --> 19:15.205
♪ Come on, show them ♪

19:15.206 --> 19:20.975
You know, I do want
to get married one day.

19:20.976 --> 19:23.065
Mm. But it won't be
in a Catholic church.

19:23.066 --> 19:25.975
Mm, I don't know about
that. The new Pope drives a Fiat.

19:25.976 --> 19:27.135
♪ Everybody's born to be different ♪

19:27.136 --> 19:31.165
But even if it's not
exactly the way you pictured it,

19:31.166 --> 19:33.075
at least there won't be a blood cannon.

19:33.076 --> 19:35.025
Well, you never know if
your sister's invited.

19:35.026 --> 19:37.045
Yeah, no, that's very true.

19:37.046 --> 19:40.085
But I hope that when I do get married,

19:40.086 --> 19:43.056
you'll be just as
excited about planning it.

19:43.334 --> 19:46.025
♪ Don't let them make you
into something you ain't ♪

19:46.026 --> 19:48.025
By the way, I'm picturing orchids.

19:48.026 --> 19:51.005
Oh, absolutely not. Orchids
are all wrong.

19:51.006 --> 19:52.085
Okay, well, obviously not by themselves.

19:52.086 --> 19:54.095
I'd want orchids and lilies.

19:54.096 --> 19:56.175
Oh! [Laughs] I'm sorry.

19:56.176 --> 19:58.085
I thought we were planning a wedding,

19:58.086 --> 20:00.105
not a Hawaiian funeral.

20:00.106 --> 20:02.095
Oh, my god!

20:02.096 --> 20:04.055
That's a fantastic idea.
It could be a luau theme!

20:04.056 --> 20:05.975
- Don't you dare.
- Come on, we could bury a pig.

20:05.976 --> 20:07.085
I can see right now

20:07.086 --> 20:08.975
I'm gonna have to start
taking over the planning.

20:08.976 --> 20:11.472
Come on, the caterers
could be fire dancers!

20:15.176 --> 20:19.065
All right, be honest with
me. Is it too drastic?

20:19.066 --> 20:20.175
I don't know what I'm looking at.

20:20.176 --> 20:21.165
Did you shave your mustache?

20:21.166 --> 20:22.270
No.

20:22.447 --> 20:24.066
I grew a beard.

20:27.026 --> 20:28.025
Oh.

20:28.026 --> 20:30.105
[Scoffs] Yeah, there it is.

20:30.106 --> 20:32.095
- Lush.
- Yeah.

20:32.096 --> 20:34.095
It's gonna be a little warm for summer.

20:34.096 --> 20:36.155
Yeah, and you're gonna get
a lot of food caught in it.

20:36.156 --> 20:37.205
Mm-hmm.

20:37.206 --> 20:39.975
[Sighs] You guys are so right.

20:39.976 --> 20:41.135
I'm gonna go shave it off.

20:41.136 --> 20:43.075
♪ ♪

20:43.076 --> 20:45.695
When we grow up, is he gonna live
in your guesthouse or mine?

20:45.853 --> 20:47.579
One, two, three.

20:47.730 --> 20:50.075
Ha ha!

20:50.076 --> 20:51.202
Ow!

